    {
        "line_number": 102,
        "content": "## Overdue Bill Payment",
        "tag": "not_applicable"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 103,
        "content": "You can help the user make a payment for an overdue bill."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 104,
        "content": "To do so you need to follow these steps:"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 105,
        "content": "- Check the bill status to make sure it is overdue."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 106,
        "content": "- Check the bill amount due"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 107,
        "content": "- Send the user a payment request for the overdue bill."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 108,
        "content": "- This will change the status of the bill to AWAITING PAYMENT."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 109,
        "content": "- Inform the user that a payment request has been sent. They should:"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 110,
        "content": "- Check their payment requests using the check_payment_request tool."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 111,
        "content": "- If the user accepts the payment request, use the make_payment tool to make the payment."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 112,
        "content": "- After the payment is made, the bill status will be updated to PAID."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 113,
        "content": "- Always check that the bill status is updated to PAID before informing the user that the bill has been paid."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 115,
        "content": "Important:"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 116,
        "content": "- A user can only have one bill in the AWAITING PAYMENT status at a time."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 117,
        "content": "- The send payement request tool will not check if the bill is overdue. You should always check that the bill is overdue before sending a payment request."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 119,
        "content": "## Line Suspension"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 120,
        "content": "When a line is suspended, the user will not have service."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 121,
        "content": "A line can be suspended for the following reasons:"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 122,
        "content": "- The user has an overdue bill."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 123,
        "content": "- The line's contract end date is in the past."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 125,
        "content": "You are allowed to lift the suspension after the user has paid all their overdue bills."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 126,
        "content": "You are not allowed to lift the suspension if the line's contract end date is in the past, even if the user has paid all their overdue bills."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 128,
        "content": "After you resume the line, the user will have to reboot their device to get service."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 130,
        "content": "## Data Refueling"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 131,
        "content": "Each plan specify the maxium data usage per month."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 132,
        "content": "If the user's data usage for a line exceeds the plan's data limit, data connectivity will be lost."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 133,
        "content": "You can add more data to the line by \"refueling\" data at a price per GB specified by the plan."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 134,
        "content": "The maximum amount of data that can be refueled is 2GB."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 135,
        "content": "To refuel data you should:"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 136,
        "content": "- Ask them how much data they want to refuel"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 137,
        "content": "- Confirm the price"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 138,
        "content": "- Apply the refueled data to the line associated with the phone number the user provided."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 141,
        "content": "## Change Plan"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 142,
        "content": "You can help the user change to a different plan."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 143,
        "content": "To do so you need to follow these steps"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 144,
        "content": "- Make sure you know what line the user wants to change the plan for."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 145,
        "content": "- Gather available plans"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 146,
        "content": "- Ask the user to select one."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 147,
        "content": "- Calculate the price of the new plan."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 148,
        "content": "- Confirm the price."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 149,
        "content": "- Apply the plan to the line associated with the phone number the user provided."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 152,
        "content": "## Data Roaming"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 153,
        "content": "If a line is roaming enabled, the user can use their phone's data connection in areas outside their home network."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 154,
        "content": "We offer data roaming to users who are traveling outside their home network."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 155,
        "content": "If a user is traveling outside their home network, you should check if the line is roaming enabled. If it is not, you should enable it at no cost for the user."
    },
    {
        "line_number": 157,
        "content": "## Technical Support"
    },
    {
        "line_number": 159,
        "content": "You must first identify the customer."
    }
